			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">The Perfect Bard<a name="52822"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 12:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As we all know, the bard is the class with the biggest coushin for player controlling the performance of their class. There is a big distinction between a horrible bard and a GREAT bard, which has nothing to do with the equipment. 
<br />

<br />
My question to the everknowing forum is simply what would make the absolute perfect bard. Most people who play bards use a lot of shortcuts, they stop switching instruments after a while, they might even sell their brass and wind completely! Lazy.
<br />

<br />
Some people have over 400 apm (actions per minute), that means they can do about 20 things every 3 seconds. which is more than enough clicks to switch instruments and weapons for songs. I feel most bards performance is limited to how fast they can move mouse and click. Well i want to know what a bard would be like if this limit wasnt there.
<br />

<br />
Consider.
<br />

<br />
1. Switching instruments with weapons while meleeing. Bards have been switching instruments when kiting for years, but not in battle. Having full instrument mods can do wonders in battle, which is done sometimes already, but not with weapons! 
<br />
The only time you actually need the instrument in hand is at the moment the song ends. Which means you can have your weapons in hand 2.9 seconds then switch the instrument in at the very last moment and switch the weapon back as soon as the song pulses. This can create a huge advantage while meleeing. Creating full instrument mods with weapons in hands at same time. You could almost throw out your epic!
<br />

<br />
2. Another thing that i think a perfect bard would be is to mez 3 mobs while fighting a 4th. The only hard part is targetting. The greatest thing about a bard is they can switch targets while casting and fight while casting. So if you could switch targets only for a moment to target a mob you arent fighting, start the mez song, then switch back to your target to fight it, then switch to the other mobs and mez them the same way. this would make an unbelievable bard.
<br />

<br />
3. You could also quad kite 4 mobs with anglist assonance, a 1 minute 2000 pt dot, takes 12 seconds to refresh + 3 second casting thats 15 seconds, 60 s/ 15s = 4 mobs dotted, + your chants in the middle, you could quad kite pretty well if you had the speed to target that well.
<br />

<br />
Please, what are your opinions or wishes that you could make your bard do if you had the speed and energy to keep up with it. These arent wishes of what bards should be able to do, these are things that a bard can do, but is limited to how fast you click and move your mouse as a player.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
