				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Perfect Bard<a name="52824"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 1:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There was a point of my bard time when I stopped Switching Instruments (epic :P). Well yea, maybe switching will do some extra dps, regen etc. but it isnt worth that work. The extra thingies are really minimal.
<br />

<br />
Mezzing 3 mobs and fighting a 4th ... Yea but 3... what about mezzing 4 mobs and fighting a 5th ?
<br />
If you saved your grp because mezzing 4mobs and still fighting with em, you will feel very good<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />believe me ;)
<br />

<br />
Quad kiting, hmm I dont think that makes a perfect bard. Sure it makes much DPS ^^ but well it isnt that kind of great, just having luck with targeting and kiting a bit.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I think a perfect bard must be able to think and act. Sometimes I meet bards, which only do what they are told. As a bard you should think and act when its needed. Thats important. Then you are a good bard, cause you can handle many situations. You must be able to know all your songs, AAs and tactics and be able to know when its time to use them, also if you dont have much time to think about what song might help now.
<br />

<br />
Yaso
<br />
</span></td>
