			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Perfect Bard<a name="52839"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 2:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Wow thats bordering on anal. At some point, a regular player will have to draw the line between having fun and chain twisting 4 instruments while mezzing 3 mobs and meleeing a 4th.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure that doing those things are interesting to you, but describing it in the sense of a perfect bard is, too, subjective.
<br />

<br />
Instrument twisting while meleeing brings far too little dps gain and doing that straight through raid lag or in a normal exp group for hours will give you a headache. Gives me a headache thinking about it! It doesn't mean I don't want to apply myself, but I think it would help my guild better in the long run if I don't burn myself out twisting instruments every night and chugging back aspirins to keep my head from throbbing.
<br />

<br />
Taken separately, I actually do practice the 2nd. In a good LDoN group I routinely pull 2-3 mobs and thats with one in camp. I will mezz them all and beat on the one the group is working on for a few seconds before retoggling to refresh mezz. With the new cycle through npcs hotkey I can do this quite easily. Mezz breaks here or there but it is a &quot;good&quot; group I'm working with so that little bit of mob damage gets shrugged off.
<br />

<br />
I just plain think the 3rd is not a great idea. Why limit to quads when you can easily AE kite 10 mobs in better time than it takes for you to bring down 4 mobs using your method? Assonance with 4.2 mod does 102/tick, a little more than that with JF3, over 1 minute. 2000 pt DoT over a minute equates to 200/tick. Your calculation here is flawed.
<br />

<br />
You have very unique ideas, I just happen to disagree.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
