				<td colspan="2"><span>My idea of a perfect bard has little to do with so many actions that draw effects that are minimally noticed by a group.  Instead, the perfect bard is one who is prepared for any situation, and knows what to do and when to do it.  A bard that keeps his group functioning smoothly, who communicates, and picks up whatever slack there may be (and then some), is a bard I would want to group with if I was any other class.</span></td>
