				<td colspan="2"><span>I pop my instruments in when my songs land all the time.  I have a 2.8 Brass that I pop in when Warsong of Zek of lands, my Epic when Psalm of Veeshan lands, and my 2.6 Lute when Chorus of Marr lands.  If the song is affected by an instrument modifier, I will almost always make sure I max out that modifier.
<br />

<br />
Three adds I do not assist.  Two adds, I still don't.  Targetting is too silly.  I toggle between my two adds, keep them mezzed, and twist in a third song, whichever is most important (Haste, Regen, Resist...)  One add, I DO attack constantly.  I face away from my mezzed mob and toggle back just long enough to START my mez song, then toggle back to my target and continue fighting and twisting.
<br />

<br />
If we ever get a charm that we can use again, I would say that I should be able to handle 5 adds again, charm one, attack a second, mez the other three.
<br />

<br />
I don't care much for what kiting exploit would be &quot;perfect&quot;.  No one else benefits, or gives you praise for it, so I don't care.  (I want the SPOTLIGHT!)</span></td>
