				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Perfect Bard<a name="53131"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 9:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have found no need to switch out instruments, but it is more because I like to melee.  It is a preference.  I switch instruments only when I am not hacking and slashing things =)
<br />

<br />
I have played around with mezzing 3 mobs and fighting the 4th, however as people noted you can accidentally remez the wrong mob and have one break free, or accidentally smack one and wake it up, so once I proved to myself I could, I stopped doing it. (if I am not tired I melee when we have 3 normal mobs, and always when we have just 2, using the same method as someone posted above.  But when mobs are 65+ and can take down the cleric in under 5 seconds, I don't have time to screw around.  If I am slow to notice, or have a hard time targetting, the cleric dies)  It wasn't worth maintaining this method all the time.  Just like the 5 song battle twist was possible, but not worth it (I am not counting the 1 minute duration songs, I just mean 5 regular songs - but my hand began cramping after about 5 minutes, so it was not fun.  However I proved to myself I could sustain it.)  I have played around with stuff like this, but as many have also said, adaptation is more important.  I have found myself memming new songs mid battle as often or more often than switching instruments.  8 song slots is just not always enough, especially when we enter a new zone and do not know what to expect =)
<br />

<br />
My recomendation is get some of the instrument modifier armor/augments/weapons and be satisfied with those for most situations.  Test your limits for fun every so often, but then sit back, relax, and twist your 4 songs (or what ever) while you beat the crap out of things =)  Even doing that i burn out after a couple of hard LDoNs or a couple hours in GoD.  I have even learned to twist with my right hand for the days when my left gets too sore, lol.  
<br />

<br />
But hurting myself to play my character is not fun, and this *IS* a game I play to have fun.  So as long as you are having fun, and not destroying other peoples fun (training them to death, being rude, etc etc) play it your way!!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Solkarr, 65th singing Battlecat of Torvo.....

